  "description": "<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p855195/\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_shuangyu.gif\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a><br /><p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2016/10/27/bf65fe342b8cf8337da9f69cc77706d1.jpg\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"><strong>Japan&mdash;The Obon, Or The Festival Of The&nbsp;</strong></span><strong><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/Lantern\" target=\"_blank\">Lanterns</a></strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"><strong>日本&mdash;&mdash;盂兰盆节，又名灯笼节</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The Festival of the Dead in Japan, which is called Obon, is held every year in the month of August. Obon is a day when the spirits return to visit their&nbsp;</span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/relative\" target=\"_blank\">relatives</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">.日本的鬼节叫&ldquo;盂兰盆节&rdquo;，时间是每年八月份。在盂兰盆节这一天，鬼魂都要回来拜访亲人。</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2016/10/27/cf35a62a702a0f5a27613171d98eac7d.jpg\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Many&nbsp;</span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/Buddhist\" target=\"_blank\">Buddhists</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;in Japan celebrate this holiday by preparing&nbsp;</span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/offering\" target=\"_blank\">offerings</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;of special food for their ancestors&rsquo; spirits, which are placed on <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/altar\" target=\"_blank\">altars</a> in temples and in their homes.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">很多日本的佛教徒过节的时候都为祖先的亡魂准备一些特殊食物作祭品，放置在寺庙和家里的供桌上。</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2016/10/27/dc193d93c328600a27c3215c2c28bf7b.jpg\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">As the sun goes down families light paper lanterns and hang them in front of their houses to help the spirits find their way home.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">太阳落山时家人就点上纸灯笼，悬挂在屋前帮助亡魂找到回家的路。</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2016/10/27/a1439d70f06f71c0bc5d75131b28ecb3.jpg\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The&nbsp;</span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/celebration\" target=\"_blank\">celebrations</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;end with families sending colorful paper lanterns&nbsp;</span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/light\" target=\"_blank\">lit</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;by candles floating down the rivers and&nbsp;</span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/bay\" target=\"_blank\">bays</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;of Japan and out to sea.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">庆祝活动的最后环节是家人在河里放彩色的纸灯笼，里面点燃蜡烛顺流而下，最后漂到大海。</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2016/10/27/b8cbe904cdc29413e81206dbb9967aef.jpg\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The string of colorful lights <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/bob\" target=\"_blank\">bobbing</a> in the water are meant to guide the spirits of their loved ones back to the&nbsp;</span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/realm\" target=\"_blank\">realm</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;of the dead.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">水面上浮动的一串串彩色光亮，是为了指引亲人的亡魂回到幽冥之地。</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2016/10/27/37ee9372f9d6d813fa3221eda75928ef.jpg\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t英语君PS：盂兰盆节也是日本一年一度的春运，全国豪堵。</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153); font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.8em;\">声明：本双语文章的中文翻译系沪江英语原创内容，转载请注明出处。中文翻译仅代表译者个人观点，仅供参考。如有不妥之处，欢迎指正。</span></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p855195/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p855195\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p795774/\">有声美文：为什么失败比成功更重要？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p725820/\">爱上新概念英语的正确方法</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p870862/\">整天宅家，脑子发霉！“宅”用英语怎么说？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p870721/\">双语食谱：10款简单又健康的早餐单品！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p854261/\">备战CET6口语：自我介绍篇</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p857798/\">今秋最值得学的10门英语课程</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p874697/\">最性感数学老师TED演讲【完整视频+字幕】</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p878267/\">杭州包子美国开分店 20元一个在哈佛卖疯了！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p876334/\">孤独星球发布2017全球最佳旅游地：说走就走！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p874615/\">BBC给咱代购取了个洋气的名字：自由零售顾问</a></li></ul><div style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">导航:  <a href=\"http://www.hujiang.com/\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" target=\"_black\">沪江网</a>  <a href=\"http://